wikipedia_page.main: Robert Hibbert (25 October 1812 – 18 December 1833) was an English cricketer with amateur status who was active in 1832. He was born in Cambridge and died in Madeira. He made his first-class debut in 1832 and appeared in two matches as an unknown handedness batsman whose bowling style is unknown, playing for Cambridge University Cricket Club. He scored ten runs with a highest score of 5 and took two wickets. He was educated at Eton and King's College, Cambridge.
